    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><persName ref="#people/3307" key="#Commutatio #childOf"
                            >Heriprando</persName>
                        <rs key="#childOf">filio</rs>
                        <persName ref="#people/3311">bone memorie Ildeprandi</persName> permuta beni
                        con <persName ref="#people/3310" key="#Bishops">Berengarius</persName>
                        gratia Dei huius Sancte Lucanem ecclesiam humulis <rs key="#Bishops"
                            >episcopus</rs> (…). Heriprando cede una <rs key="#Petiae">petia de
                            terra</rs> quod est chasalino in loco <geogName ref="#estates/1702"
                            key="#Confinia #Curtes #Mother_churches"><placeName ref="#places/431"
                                key="#Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Mention #Roads #Cisterns/pits #Bridges/pontoons #Queen"
                                >Capannule</placeName>, prope <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs> vestra
                                <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/68" key="#Curtes">Sancti
                                Martini</orgName></geogName>, qui <rs key="#Confinia">uno caput
                            tene</rs> in <rs key="#Roads">via publica</rs>, alio caput in <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Mention #Queen">terra domne
                            Regine</rs>, lato uno in <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        suprascripte ecclesie <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/68"
                            key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions #Mother_churches">Sancti
                            Martini</orgName> et alio latus in <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Mention #Queen">terra domne
                            Regine</rs>. Petia ipsa (…) excepto exinde <rs key="#Stone #Woad"
                            >lignamen et petre</rs> et cum omnen edeficio seo movile de casa (…)
                        quas mihi reservo exinde tollendi et faciendi quod voluerimus. Similiter et
                        (…) una <rs key="#Petiae">alia petia de terra</rs> ubi dicitur <placeName
                            ref="#places/431" key="#Confinia #Petiae #Cisterns/pits">ad <rs
                                key="#Cisterns/pits">fossa <persName key="#Cisterns/pits"><name
                                        ref="Radaldus">Radaldi</name></persName></rs></placeName>
                        qui <rs key="#Confinia">uno caput tene</rs> in <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terra</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions" ref="#juridical_persons/610"
                            >Sancti Savini</orgName>, alio caput in <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Mention #Queen">terra domne
                            Regine</rs>, lato uno tene in fossa qui dicitur Radaldi et alio lato in
                            <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <persName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions"><name ref="Ostrifunsus"
                                >Ostrifusi</name></persName>. <rs key="#Petiae">Tertia petia</rs>
                        (…) in loco ubi dicitur <placeName key="#Confinia #Rivers #Petiae"
                            ref="#places/431">ad Rivo</placeName>, qui <rs key="#Confinia">uno caput
                            tene</rs> in ipso Rivo, alio caput in <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terra</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions" ref="#juridical_persons/610"
                            >Sancti Savini</orgName>, lato uno in <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terra</rs>
                        <persName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions"><name ref="Alamundus"
                                >Alamundi</name></persName> et alio latus tene in <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions" ref="#juridical_persons/610"
                            >Sancti Savini</orgName>. Simul et (…) <rs key="#Petiae">quarta
                            petia</rs> de terra ubi dicitur ad <placeName ref="#places/431"
                            key="#Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Roads #Bridges/pontoons"
                            >Vepre Burduli</placeName> prope <rs key="#Bridges/pontoons">ponte</rs>,
                        et <rs key="#Confinia">est uno caput tenente</rs> in <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions" ref="#juridical_persons/230"
                            >Sancti Petri</orgName>, alio caput in <rs key="#Roads">via
                        publica</rs>, lato uno in Rivo et alio lato in <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terra</rs>
                        <rs key="#Churches">ecclesie</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/269">Sancte Marie</orgName>. Et <rs
                            key="#Petiae">quinta petia</rs> de terra quod est <rs key="#Hay/fodder"
                            >prato</rs> ubi dicitur <placeName ref="#places/431"
                            key="#Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Mention"
                            >ad Termine</placeName> qui <rs key="#Confinia">uno caput tene</rs> in
                            <rs key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Mention #Queen">terra
                            domne Regine</rs> alio caput in <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/2013" key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions"
                            >Sancti Benedicti</orgName> lato uno in <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terra</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions" ref="#juridical_persons/269"
                            >Sancte Marie</orgName> et <orgName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2033">Sancti Fridiani</orgName> et alio lato in
                            <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <persName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions"><name ref="Aginus"
                                >Eghini</name></persName>. Predicte quinque petie de terra (…) sunt
                        tote insimul ad musta perticha mensurate <rs key="#Size">modiorum decem et
                            nove et sistariorum undecim</rs> (…). Riceve in cambio una <rs
                            key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions #Cafagia">petia de terra quod est
                            cafagio</rs> in loco ubi dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Cafagia #Fiscal_property #Mention"
                            ref="#places/3337">Cantiniano</placeName> prope <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio
                            Rogglo</rs> pertenens ecclesie vestre <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3323" key="#Mother_churches">Sancti
                            Iusti</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Mother_churches">plebe baptismalis</rs> sita in loco <placeName
                            ref="#places/3237" key="#Baptismal_churches">Padule</placeName> de
                        suppotestatem <rs key="#Domus #Mother_churches">domi episcopatui</rs> vestri
                            <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/68" key="#Domus #Mother_churches"
                            >Sancti Martini</orgName>, et <rs key="#Confinia">est tenente uno
                            caput</rs> in <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/79">Sancti Petri de <placeName
                                ref="#places/85" key="#Monasteries">Monte
                            Viride</placeName></orgName> et in terra mea, alio caput tene in <rs
                            key="#Cisterns/pits">fossa Docaria</rs> quod est da partibus exurgente,
                        lato uno tene in terra mea et in aliquantulo in <rs key="#Forests"
                            >silva</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/79" key="#Confinia #Forests">Sancti Petri
                            de <placeName ref="#places/85" key="#Monasteries">Monte
                                Viride</placeName></orgName> et alio latus tene similiter in terra
                        mea et in aliquantulo in <rs key="#Wine">vinea</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/79" key="#Confinia #Wine">Sancti Petri de
                                <placeName ref="#places/85" key="#Monasteries">Monte
                                Viride</placeName></orgName>. Hec predica petia (…) est per mensura
                        ad iusta perticha mensurata <rs key="#Size">modiorum decem et octo et
                            sistariorum sidecim et dimidio</rs> (…). Ubi et super hanc comutationem
                        direxisti <rs key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities">missos vestros</rs>
                        idest <persName key="#Witness #Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Priests"
                                ><name ref="Bernardus">Bernardus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbitero adque vicedomui</rs> vestri seo <persName
                            key="#Witness #Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name ref="Alpertus"
                                >Alipertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbitero</rs> et <persName
                            key="#Witness #Missus_of_other_public_authorities #vassusOf"><name
                                ref="Ebrohac">Ebrohac</name></persName> adque <persName
                            key="#Witness #Missus_of_other_public_authorities #vassusOf"><name
                                ref="Alpertus">Alperto</name></persName> [filio <persName>bone
                            memorie <name ref="Radibrandus">Rapprandi</name></persName> - tratto
                        dalla sottoscrizione] <rs>vassalli vestri</rs> qui ambulaverunt et
                        previderunt hac renuntiaverunt quod meliorata comutationem (…). Pena in
                        duplum (…). <persName key="#Writer #Notary"><name ref="Teofridus"
                                >Teufridi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> scrive due <rs key="#Commutatio"
                            >cartulas</rs>. Actum <placeName ref="#places/4"
                            key="#Mother_churches #Bishops">Luca</placeName>.</ab>
                    <ab>Oltre ai due missi sottoscrivono come <rs key="#Witness">testimoni</rs>:
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Gausprandus"
                            >Gausprandu</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Scabini #Other_clerics"><name ref="Iohannes"
                                >Iohannis</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Scabini #Other_clerics">clericus scavinu</rs>, <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Leoprandus">Leoprandus</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Gumbertus"
                            >Gumpertu</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Andreas">Andreas</name></persName> filio <persName>bone memorie
                                <name ref="Ildefredus">Iltifridi</name></persName>, <persName
                            ref="#people/211" key="#Witness">Teudimundus</persName>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>ChLA, 77, n. 50, pp. 152-155; MDL, 5/3, App., n. 1763, pp. 635-636 (datazione
                    sbagliata) </p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
                <p>Sulla presenza di beni fiscali nella zona e, in generale, in Valdera, vd.
                    Schneider 1975, pp. 232-233; sull’analisi del documento e delle confinanze, vd.
                    Collavini 1998, pp. 40-44, 64-66; Viti 2019-2020, pp. 132-134.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="links">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Sottoscrizioni autografe: Eriprandus, Bernardus presbiter (misso), Alipertus
                    presbiter (misso), Gausprandu, Iohannis clericus scavinu, Leoprandus, Gumpertu,
                    Teudimundus, Teufridi notarius (scrittore). Sottoscrizioni con
                        <foreign>Signa</foreign>: Alperto qd. Rapprandi (misso), Ebrohac (misso),
                    Andreas qd. Iltifridi.  Note tergali: in alto al centro, di mano del rogatario:
                        <foreign>+ Viganeum da Heriprando</foreign>; in basso di mano dei secc.
                    XI-XII: <foreign>Hęc carta clamat t(er)ra(m) in plebe d(e) Padule</foreign>;
                    preceduta dal nome <foreign>Heriprandus</foreign> vergato da mano del secolo
                    XIII che, poco sopra, annota: <foreign>Capa(n)ule. \ Heripra(n)d(us)</foreign>;
                    in alto di mano del secolo XIII: <foreign>(Com)mutatio i(n)t(er) Heriprandu(m)
                        (et) ep(iscopu)m Luc(ensem) d(e) q(ui)b(us)da(m) t(er)ris (et) casis i(n)
                        Capan(n)ul(is)</foreign>.</p>
                <p>Per le chiese <foreign>Sancte Marie et Sancti Fridiani</foreign> menzionate tra
                    gli enti confinanti come comproprietarie di un appezzamento di terra in
                    Capannoli indichiamo San Frediano di Lucca e Santa Maria di Sesto di Moriano
                    (Lucca). Le due chiese, infatti, sono attestate già nel 774 come comproprietarie
                    di una vigna situato in <foreign>Metjano</foreign>, nella regione di Brancoli
                    (Lucca), vd. ChLA, 36, n. 1047. Non possiamo comunque escludere l’ipotesi che si
                    tratti di altre chiese (forse la chiesa valdarnese di Santa Maria a Monte?) o
                    quella - a mio avviso più improbabile - di una doppia dedicazione. La prima
                    attestazione di beni appartenenti alla basilica lucchese di San Frediano in
                    Capannoli risale all’anno 818, vd. ChLA, 74, n. 34. </p>
            </div>
